                  <p/>
Most animals like to work for their food. Animals that dig for food, such as 
                  <a href="zoopedia:zoopedia_beaver:entry">
                     <u>
                        <color r="255" g="231" b="135">American beavers</color>
                     </u>, 
                  </a>
                  <a href="zoopedia:zoopedia_gorilla:entry">
                     <u>
                        <color r="255" g="231" b="135">mountain gorillas</color>
                     </u>, 
                  </a>
                  <a href="zoopedia:zoopedia_warthoggiant:entry">
                     <u>
                        <color r="255" g="231" b="135">warthogs</color>
                     </u>, 
                  </a>and 
                  <a href="zoopedia:zoopedia_gigantopithecus:entry">
                     <u>
                        <color r="255" g="231" b="135">Gigantopithecuses</color>,
                     </u>
                  </a>                  
 enjoy eating roots.  

                  <p/>
Place roots on the ground or in a food dish, substrate pile, or trough.
